Oh! I got it!

It turns out the [docs](https://reactjs.org/docs/test-utils.html#act) mention synchronous functions like this:

```
act( () =&gt; {
  // ... some &#39;sync logic&#39;
});
```
which you can&#39;t await.

But you can await an async function of course:

```
await act( async () =&gt; {
  // ... some &#39;async logic&#39;
});
```

This fixed the problem for me.

